{"date":"Mon, 14 Sep 2020 00:45:33 GMT","img_url":"https://english.khabarhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Bidhya-Bhandari.jpg","keywords":["ensure","president","child","the","that","khabarhub","has","of","calls","rights","to","bhandari","and","by","national"],"summary":"President Bhandari calls to ensure child rightsKATHMANDU: President Bidya Devi Bhandari has asked three-tier of governments, national and international non-governmental agencies, civil society and guardians to be more sensitive to ensure child rights in the current difficult situation created by the pandemic coronavirus infection.\nIn a message today on the occasion of the National Children\u2019s Day 2077, the President has stated that it was the state responsibility to effectively implement national laws and different international treaties, agreements and commitments made by the government to ensure child rights.\nSaying that getting quality education was the children\u2019s rights, the President mentioned that three-tier of governments, national and international agencies, community sectors, the media and civil society are taking steps to make schools the centre of attraction by creating child-friendly academic environment.\nPresident Bhandari has also recalled that the government has taken the policy of zero-tolerance on violence against children while adding that the government has taken the policy of child protection system by providing guardianship to the hapless and needy children.\nThe President has praised the learning activities through alternate medium during the time of pandemic and expected commitment of all to translate the national aspiration of \u2018Prosperous Nepal, Happy Nepalis\u2019 by being sincere to the protection and development of today\u2019s children.","text":"President Bhandari calls to ensure child rights\n\nKATHMANDU: President Bidya Devi Bhandari has asked three-tier of governments, national and international non-governmental agencies, civil society and guardians to be more sensitive to ensure child rights in the current difficult situation created by the pandemic coronavirus infection.\n\nIn a message today on the occasion of the National Children\u2019s Day 2077, the President has stated that it was the state responsibility to effectively implement national laws and different international treaties, agreements and commitments made by the government to ensure child rights.\n\nSaying that getting quality education was the children\u2019s rights, the President mentioned that three-tier of governments, national and international agencies, community sectors, the media and civil society are taking steps to make schools the centre of attraction by creating child-friendly academic environment.\n\nPresident Bhandari has also recalled that the government has taken the policy of zero-tolerance on violence against children while adding that the government has taken the policy of child protection system by providing guardianship to the hapless and needy children.\n\nThe President has praised the learning activities through alternate medium during the time of pandemic and expected commitment of all to translate the national aspiration of \u2018Prosperous Nepal, Happy Nepalis\u2019 by being sincere to the protection and development of today\u2019s children.\n\nRSS","title":"President Bhandari calls to ensure child rights - Khabarhub","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2020/14/127269/","video":[]}
